        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 2:11PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 211 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
New Waverly, or 7 miles north of Willis, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Huntsville, New Waverly, and Huntsville State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
